  "intro": "Phil Ford (born 1960) is a British television writer. He was head writer from the second series of The Sarah Jane Adventures, broadcast in 2008, wrote The Waters of Mars, one of the 2009 special episodes of Doctor Who, with Russell T Davies. and wrote the majority of the 2010s video game series . In 2012, with Davies, he created Wizards vs Aliens which ran for three series. He won a Hugo Award, a Writers' Guild Award and was four-times BAFTA nominated."
